      Yes. Lightly brushing plants daily can simulate movement and strengthen stems.
    </p>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Will a fan fix leggy seedlings?</summary>
    <p>
      No. Insufficient light is usually the primary cause of legginess.
    </p>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Do cool-season crops need airflow?</summary>
    <p>
      All seedlings benefit from airflow, though shorter indoor duration reduces urgency.
    </p>
  </details>

  <details>
    <summary>Is this different in Canada?</summary>
    <p>
      The principles are universal. Indoor conditions determine outcomes.
    </p>
  </details>
</section>

